I was refering to pre 4.8 versions of Bind.  These ones did not
put a clamp on the ttl and used what was given in the cache file
instead of verifying the data.  Current servers won't answer a
query (except for an error response) they are not authoritative
for until they have received a list of root servers from one of
the servers listed in the cache file.

				Jim

